Description: Levels: Advanced  Professional  Semi-Pro  Absolute Beginners. Anyone seeking to learn or further develop jazz  rock  and classical guitar. BEGINNER CONTENT:  All basic chords  strums  fingerpicking  songs  sing and play  read music.  WHY I‚ÄôM DIFFERENT: I provide 24/7 support  lesson notes  jam tracks (full band) customized for your practice  videos of lesson material organized on your computer/phone app  ear training program  and more.  My students express that they learn more from me in just a few lessons than with previous teachers they've had for years. I'm an enthusiastic and supportive teacher who makes lessons enjoyable  valuable  practical  and highly instructional with results. If you are serious and passionate about advancing your guitar playing  contact me and start playing as you've always dreamed.  ABOUT ME: ‚Ä¢11 years experience as a professional NYC musician on Broadway  at Carnegie Hall and other NYC venues. ‚Ä¢Master's Degree M.M. Guitar Performance/Pedagogy ‚Ä¢Director of Guitar Studies at University of Toledo teaching jazz and classical guitar  ensembles  jazz combos  music theory  music history  and more! ‚Ä¢Adjunct professor in Jazz Guitar at University of Michigan. ‚Ä¢Guitar Player Magazine columnist ‚Ä¢Performed and toured with top entertainers and musicians including legendary jazz vocalist Jon Hendricks   CONNECT: FB: edlevylessons FB: edlevymusic IG: edlevymusic  For more information  please reply to this ad or send me a message on "edlevylessons" FB page. If you're serious about playing guitar  stop by and say hi!  TESTIMONIALS  "In 2019  I took several 1-hour lessons from Ed Levy  master Broadway guitarist/teacher. Ed is based in New York City; I live in San Diego; so  naturally  we used SKYPE to conduct our lessons. SKYPE worked out great. It allowed me to avail myself of Ed‚Äôs musical expertise  something I couldn‚Äôt get face-to-face here in San Diego. The value of Ed‚Äôs lessons was inestimable. As a classical guitarist/composer  I was interested in learning more music theory so I could better understand the nature of my instrument. Ed‚Äôs lessons did not disappoint! Not only did I learn the 5 major scale patterns in 5 keys and was given the major  4-note root position chord voicings  but Ed‚Äôs enthusiasm for the entire jazz genre ignited a spark in me that has now led to a lifelong interest in the jazz idiom. I can‚Äôt wait to resume my lessons with Ed.  Jerry K.  classical guitarist / San Diego  CA  "I studied with Ed Levy while working on my Bachelor's Degree. He has helped me tremendously in the areas that would have otherwise been very daunting and difficult to learn  such as arranging chord-melody solos  learning to play over difficult chord changes  transcribing and analyzing solos  to name a few. Ed has helped me with understanding music theory  fretboard knowledge  and selection of good repertoire. He also instilled the love and appreciation of Classical Guitar playing. Ed is a very high-caliber musician  and has a wealth of knowledge of modern concepts of approaching harmony and rhythm.   Peter K.  guitarist/music teacher  Master's of Music Degree Program  "Ed is a phenomenal teacher. I began with no musical knowledge at all. I did not know how to hold a guitar or a pick and today my guitar is a daily joy. The amount Ed taught me is amazing. I now have rhythm  an understanding of musical theory and structure  can read and write music and can hear music in an entirely different way as well as being able to play with friends.  Glenn M.  "I am a video/audio engineer and programmer for a large A/V integrator as well as a guitarist/vocalist currently with Lenox Underground  a classic rock cover band based in Summit NJ. The musical devices and knowledge he has picked up along his career path have all been compiled and polished as an effective and speedy track to better playing.   Brian H.  guitar/vocals/engineer & programmer (Diversified US)  "Ed Levy is great  he was my first guitar teacher at UT  and taught me what is now my favorite chord (V7sus4b9).This dude got my classical chops from Snowflight to Capricho Arabe  and showed me how to love jazz. I also have to consider gas to get to an event. And further more I have to consider the value of my equipment and the cost depreciation. I own my equipment  and I use the top of the line. A lot of people hiring a DJ do not understand how much work this job entails. Thank you for your time and I appreciate you reading my ad.
